<http://www.spektrix.com/gatewaytheatre/event/74601AKVNBMMSQGJNLBBTGQBNSQMLHPDK> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "[2026]Where Have All the Buffalo Gone?";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Where Have All The Buffalo Gone?</h1><span><br/></span>An Axis Theatre Company Production<span><br/></span>Presented by Gateway Theatre<span><br/></span>A Theatre for Young Audiences Show<span><br/></span>Performed for a live audience in Studio B<span><br/></span>Run time: approximately 55 minutes with no intermission<span><br/></span>Recommended for Ages 9+<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>By Tai Amy Grauman<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">February 16 - 23, 2026</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Where Have All The Buffalo Gone?</span> follows two souls as they journey through seven important moments in Metis history – from the birth of Metis nations on the plains to the colonization driven by the fur trade, the disappearance of the buffalo, and the rise of the Metis Association of Alberta.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This moving tale weaves together stories and a life-like buffalo puppet, with true historical events to explore the love, loss, and resilience of Treaty 6’s Metis peoples. At its heart, this story celebrates the rich lessons and love stories of the buffalo. This Theatre for Young Audiences production is perfect to be enjoyed by youth ages 9 and up and is a great way to celebrate family day.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tickets from $13.50</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
